defaultIt is our deep conviction, borne out of our personal experiences, and confirmed by the impact of our activities, that promoting mutual understanding of the other within Israeli and Palestinian societies at the grass roots level is central to resolving the 
defaultconflict. The most powerful way to do this, and the most challenging, is to bring Israelis and Palestinians face to face in a spirit of open dialogue, and not confrontation. Prior to the Second Intifada contact between the two societies was far greater. Th
defaultat 
defaultdesperate period of conflict greatly deepened the
default emotional and physical wedge between the two populations. 
defaultToday we are struggling against the challenging political situation and the physical barriers
default that separate us
default which
default shut down the space for dia
defaultlogue, reduce understanding, and reinforce hardline positions on both sides.  
defaultIn the context of the considerable sums spent by international donors with the aim of promoting peace between Israelis and Palestinians, we believe that grass roots reconciliati
defaulton projects like ours are a critically important investment. 
defaultWe urge the UK government to give priority accordingly to grassroots reconciliation efforts
default that
default educate each side about the other and bring Israelis and Palestinians 
defaultto the understanding that no
defaultn-violence is the only solution to this never ending conflict
default.
