defaultYouth Education
defaultThe personal stories of our members hold special significance for
default&#xa0;
defaultthe younger generation.
default&#xa0;
defaultOur
default high school dialogue meetings address young Israeli and Palestinian students.
default&#xa0;
defaultSince the 
defaultS
defaultecond Intifada there is a whole generation who have never met the “other side” and the dialogue meetings may be their first encounter.
default&#xa0;
default After hearing
default&#xa0;
defaultthe personal nar
defaultratives and the joint message of an Israeli and a Palestinian representative from the PCFF in their classroom, there is a
default&#xa0;
defaultdefinite change in attitude and a willingness to explore the possibility of a dialogue as an alternative to violence and an understand
defaulting of the needs of the other. 
default&#xa0;
defaultWe know that these encounters work by the interesting and often very poignant feedback forms students fill in at the end of the meeting.
default&#xa0;
defaultWe manage to reach an average of 15,000 students each year.
default&#xa0;
defaultWe have a follow up meeting
default with the students which includes the screening of “Two Sided Story”
default&#xa0;
defaulta documentary produced by the Parents Circle – Families Forum, which illustrates the narrative of both sides.
default&#xa0;
defaultThis documentary is based on an adult workshop run by the PCFF.
