defaultThe PCFF launched the Crack in the Wall (CITW)
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default(
defaulthttp://www.facebook.com/crackinthewall
default)
default&#xa0;
default in order to foster interaction between Palestinians and Is
defaultraelis and to facilitate more opportunities for changing attitudes, breaking down stereotypes and humanizing the conflicted societies in order to break the cycle of violence.
default&#xa0;
default The uniqueness of this network is that all its entries are published in Hebrew a
defaultnd Arabic
default,
default allowing users to express themselves in their own language.
default&#xa0;
defaultResearch has shown that technologies of communication like social media platforms have an enabling effect.
default&#xa0;
defaultThey have acted as a catalyst to facilitate and accelerate social change alrea
defaultdy happening on the ground. Since the Crack in the Wall was launched in April 2012 it has provided a platform for more than 20,000 people, the majority of them Israelis and Palestinians.
default&#xa0;
defaultIt has brought to the forefront the fact that there are Israelis and 
defaultPalestinians who want to be engaged and who are determined to work together to 
defaultchange the
default status quo. In 2013 the Crack in the Wall project won the prestigious 
defaultUnited Nations Alliance of Civilizations (UNAOC)
default/BMW
default&#xa0;
defaultaward.
